#
# Copyright (C) 2025 Teltonika-Networks
#

#
# Documentation
#
# STRUCTURE:
# ----------
# 1. Labels - Define major feature categories
#    Usage: label "Category Name"
#    Example: label "Mobile Management"
#
# 2. Detail - Provides descriptive text about features (supports multiple lines)
#    Usage: detail [if CONDITION]
#               [key]: Descriptive text
#
#    The [key]: prefix is optional:
#    - With prefix: Uses the specified key as the feature name
#    - Without prefix: Uses the feature's title as the key automatically
#
#    Examples:
#    With prefix:    detail
#                        Band's management: Provides mobile band locking for different network types
#
#    Without prefix: detail
#                        Enables tracking of mobile data usage across daily, weekly, monthly periods
#
# 3. Tooltip - Provides additional explanatory information (supports multiple lines)
#    Usage: tooltip [key|value] [if CONDITION]
#               [detail_key]: Additional information about the feature
#
#    The [detail_key]: prefix is optional:
#    - With prefix: Uses the specified key to link to specified detail key
#    - Without prefix: Uses the feature's title as the key automatically
#
#    The type can be 'key' or 'value' (defaults to 'key' if omitted)
#    It specifies the place where the tooltip should be shown.
#
#    Examples:
#    With prefix:    tooltip key
#                        eSIM management: Feature availability varies by order code
#
#    Without prefix: tooltip key
#                        Feature availability varies by order code
#
# SPECIAL FORMATTING:
# ------------------
# 1. Escaping colons - Use "\:" to include literal colons in text
#    Example: detail
#                 Teltonika RMS https\://teltonika-networks.com/products/rms
#
# 2. Joining text - Text from multiple detail/tooltip blocks is joined with spaces
#    • Default behavior: Adds space between blocks
#    • Escaped joining: Use "\" at the beginning of a line to join without extra space
#
#    Example:
#    detail
#        Certificate creation tool allows to create CA, server, client
#    detail if LETS_ENCRYPT_SUPPORT
#        \, let's encrypt
#    detail if SCEP_SUPPORT
#        \, SCEP
#    detail
#        certificates
#
#    Result: "Certificate creation tool allows to create CA, server, client, let's encrypt, SCEP certificates"
#


#
# Labels
#

